>sight.  If you are just floating above the target, any serious hit on the
>drives results in the death-dive of all time :-), while if you are in
>orbit at least you get a chance to do repairs or surrender.

Of course, if you make yourself a duck without securing the pond first, you
deserve to die. Even if you are in geosynchronous orbit, you can still pull
out to safety - you just have to give up your spot.

