scream 
>"unfair, its not in the rules" when their gizmos break down.....
>

When I was refereeing a campaign that was one of my favorite devices to make 
life more interesting.  Particularly when I had a well equipped party.

Another concept that I had in the back of my mind was that a high tech item 
was developed on a particular world.  There *could* be reasons why that high 
tech piece of gear would not work on another world.  Fer instance, 
environmental.  If (to take an extreme example) the world that an item was 
developed and tested on was a desert world and you take that item to a world 
that is a highly humid place it might start screwing up at the worst 
possible moment.

A "Rambo" type PC that was playing in one of my campaigns discovered that on 
a rather low tech world where he thougth he would be preeminiant with his 
ACR with every bell and whistle known to sophontkind discovered that the 
high pollen counts caused the action of his weapon to require cleaning more 
often than normal.  Otherwise the weapon "stovepiped" on him.  And did.  In 
