    'body' => 'For what it\'s worth:

    In the first three months of 1995, the Port of New Orleans processed just
over 2.77 million tons (metric) of "general
cargo" and just under 27.7 million tons (metric) of "bulk
cargo".
    The Port of Houston did a similar amount of business
(slightly more, actually...)
    Note that these figures are for imports and exports, NOT
transshipments within the USA.

    The total for the two ports translates to just over 4.3 million
displacement tons of cargo as Trav counts such things.  That
is nearly 18,000 displacement tons of cargo per _day_ at each of the two
ports.

    The thing to keep in mind is that these two ports are far
from the busiest ports in the USA, and that the USA is a
pop-8 nation by Trav standards.  A world like Trin, with a
population 40 times what we have in the USA should have
correspondingly high traffic at its ports...
    Think about it...

                                    ----Steve

