    'subj' => 'Vermin in the Pipework',
    'month' => '05',
    'index' => 'ab396',
    'topic' => 'Vermin in the Pipework',
    'body' => 'A few points:

Vermin can include bugs, bacteria, etc. \'Pipework\'-related health problems
in the UK are less \'rats and cockroaches\' (although they certainly pop up in
some places!) but more \'nasty bacteria\', etc. growing in air cooling systems.

Vacuum might kill the big things but you\'re still thinking "Earth" here -
you should be thinking "Alien" - i.e. there will be bugs that don\'t care if
you evacuate their air. I\'m pretty certain evacuation won\'t kill all
bacteria, etc. Then there\'s toxins in the system (overheated synthetic
materials giving off poison gas, recyclers not working properly), and the
problem that evacuating every month still leaves the other 27 days for
vermin, et al to accumulate.

Has anyone ever actually had their players volunteer: "Hey guys, it\'s time
for us all to suit up and evacuate the ship in case we\'ve got rats on
board"... I shouldn\'t think so!

Anyone subjected their players to finding an ant or wasps nest in their air
system?
"C\'mon Jack, get that suit on"
"Fred! I\'m doing it as fast as-"
"Hell, listen to that buzz - they know we\'re on to them"
"All done. Ready to Evac"
HISSSSSSSSSSSSSSSSSS...
"Yo! Take that suckers"
HISSSS...
"Er, Jack"
SSSS...
"Yeh, yeh, what is it?"
SS...
"I can still hear the buzz"
"Don\'t be stupid - in space, no one can hear you buzz"
"Er, Jack, I can definitely-"
"Fred, er, that means, er-"
"Oh God. Ah! Oooh! They sting! Damn!"
"Get out of the suit Fred! Get out!"
"Arrrgh! Get the bloody pressure back up! OOOOOH!"

There are, of course, other measures. IMHC (In My Humble Campaign) ship air
systems have electrified grids and mini trundling robots in between to keep
out nasties and sweep up any resulting mess...

Andy Lilly

