    'topic' => '3D Space, Merchant Princes, & Computers',
    'body' => 'To all who read this List, Greetings.

As a GM who (i): has recently returned-to-the-classic-Traveller-fold 
(my home-grown campaign concluded [?] *way* back in 1988), and (ii): 
has only just the other day discovered this list, there are several 
observations/questions I would pose.

For several years now a thought has been niggling at me. Traveller 
seemed to lack something - and that something was a 3rd dimension to 
the universe. As an abstract, the official Traveller universe existed 
soley as a linear concept. For example: the Spinward Main moved in a 
series of straight lines from flat subsector map to flat subsector map 
(and there\'s nothing at all wrong with this). 

However, with the simple addition of several maps above (and below) a 
subsector, the Universe becomes 3 dimensional (cubic space). This, of 
course, can be a boon for (i): jump-1 Free Traders, as a whole new 
network of feeder routes will open up; (ii): budding AstroNavigators;
or (iii): GM\'s when a misjump catapultes a ship that random 6d6 number 
of parsecs off course :)  The best way to represent such a working 
model is to photocopy the requesite number of subsector maps (3 is 
good, 5 is better) onto acetate and to layer them one atop the other. 
It adds a whole new dimension to the game ...

As there have doubtlessly been many refinements to classic Traveller 
in the field of Trade and Economics, are there any Digests I should 
look at in particular? My campaign is *very* much a Merchant Prince 
one [I think that PC\'s discharged weapons maybe half a dozen times in 
6 years of campaigning - and I\'d like to keep it that way, thank you 
:)] in a home-grown universe based on Anderson, Cherryh, Norton, et 
al. Any other Merchant Princes out there?

My second question relates to computers. Since Traveller was 
published, computers have progressed way beyond the simple models 
represented (especially in the fields of capacity, and performance). 
Could anyone please point me in the direction of new material/updates 
et cetera regards computers in the *classic* Traveller universe [my 
finances don\'t stretch that far to purchasing MT or New Generation - 
even secondhand :(]

Thanking you in advance.

Regards,
- Dorian


