    'body' => '     >>For several years now a thought has been niggling at me. Traveller 
     seemed to lack something - and that something was a 3rd dimension to 
     the universe. As an abstract, the official Traveller universe existed 
     soley as a linear concept. For example: the Spinward Main moved in a 
     series of straight lines from flat subsector map to flat subsector map 
     (and there\'s nothing at all wrong with this). 
     
     This is true, but for ease of use, I\'ve decided to apply a fair degree 
     of suspension of disbelief.  One way _I\'m_ able to rationalize it is 
     that even though the starmaps appear 2d, one can argue that the 
     planets are actually set "above" and "below" each other to a fair 
     degree.  While liberal use of the Pythagorean Theorem and laws of 
     cosines and sines could give you an accurate figure, let\'s face it, 
     Traveller\'s jump drive rules are relatively inexact.
     
     I\'d like to think that the Traveller universe already _is_ 3d, but 
     that the maps just show a slightly myopic depiction of what\'s actually 
     in space.
     
     I guess it all depends on the level of detail you want to have.  For 
     me, all the mathematical calculations takes away from what I really 
     want to do:  roleplay.
     
