language and back, without keeping the same number of characters, it was
based on prime number congruences with some extras. The alphabet I used
was ..Etruscan.....[He immediately recognized it..]).

On a different subject, has anybody understood the logic behind having local
nobles interfering with the Navy? I was shocked when I read that in rebellion
(I had not realized it was that bad until that time..). History tells us
that one of the best ways to achieve complete failure in a military mission
is to have the politicians influence the military (see, e.g., Winston
Churchill during WW I..).

If the influence of politicians is so large, one could also understand why
the Imperial Ships (as sketched in Shattered Ships) are so expensive and
inefficient. In my Universe the first thing Norris has done as a Grand Duke
is to protect the military from political/noble interference and to
start designing/building new more efficient battleships.

                               Max



