dictator. Most war crimes during the Rebellion seems to be
committed by Lucan\'s forces.

>(not to mention that if I were Lucan I would have had psionic body
>guards from the Marches to scan visitors minds..)

Anyway, the fact that Lucan isn\'t dead yet indicates that he\'s a
cunning, maybe even intelligent person. That makes him even
scarier.

>My guess is that this is to make it a better world to roleplay
>rather than a better world to live.

The Rebellion was invented with the sole purpose of making the
Imperium a better place to roleplay in. This was discussed in an
article in the Travellers\' Digest #12.

It doesn\'t seem to me, though, that the pre-Rebellion Imperium
was a better or worse place to live than modern day Terra. The
worlds are autonomously controlled, and, like the real world, there
are good and bad places. The organizational structure of the
Imperium doesn\'t affect the citizens.

Mark Seemann
