MAX\'S DESIGNS FOR THE IRIDIUM BRIGADE

Under Max\'s Modular Combat Vehicle System (MCVS) the craft all have the same
key 
features (further details in Digests 300 +):

* Same Power Plant, Grav Thrust, Sensors, Commo, Decoy launchers, Environment
* All have no EMM Level

TYPES OF VEHICLES AND ACRONYMS

MBGT - Main Battle Grav Tank (modern day equivalent: M1A2 Abrams (US), 
Challenger 2 (UK), Leopard II (Germany), Le Clerc (France)

IFV (APC) - Infantry Fighting Vehicle (modern day equivalent: M2 Bradley
(US), 
Warrior (UK), Marder (Germany), BMP-3 (Russia), AMX (France)

CGT - Cavalry Grav Tank (Modern day equivalents: M3 Bradley (US), Scorpion, 
Scimatar (UK))

HKV - Hunter Killer Vehicle (mobile anti-tank missile launchers etc.)

ADV - Air Defence Vehicle (modern day equivalents: ZSU-23-4 (Russia), M113 
Vulcan (USA), Chapparal (US), Mobile Rapier (UK))

FIST - heavy FIre SupporT vehicle (modern day equivalents (indirect fire):
M109 
Paladin (US))

