    'index' => 'ab473',
    'body' => '> On earth today
> the countries with the highest production TL (and this is what the
> TL is) are less violent than the ones with lower TL.

Right now, that is possibly true.  (Although Japanese prisons do things that
have been illegal in North America for decades, and the Japanese TL is
equivalent to North America\'s.)

However, just half a century ago this was not the case.  Look at the German,
Russian, Japanese, American, and Canadian human rights record during WWII.

During the Renaissance, when technology was improving at a phenominal rate,
violence in everyday life reached record levels.  The most technologically
advanced societies were also the most violent.  Assault and murder were
commonplace, and even kings were powerless to stop casual killing in their
courts.

Even right now, authorities are often powerless.  Canadian visitors to
Detroit are often escorted to the Tunnel by the Detroit police when they
stray into the wrong areas after dark - apparently people in Detroit know
which neighbourhoods to avoid.  Same thing applies in New York City.  (In
fact, an acquaintance of mine in counter-terrorism tells of how the FBI
delayed a raid until after dawn because there were areas _they_ didn\'t go
into after dark!)  Carjacking, home invasion... all have skyrocketed in
recent years, along with technology.

You are, of course, free to run your universe as you choose.  In my Traveller
universe, advancing technology has not changed human nature, because I can
find no historical evidence that human nature is changing.
