    'body' => 'Max says:
>Two possible reasons:
>1- higher TL = better lifestyle, more money = less will to kill
>and torture somebody else for silly reasons

>2- higher TL = higher development = higher general cultural
>development(and this is a fact of history, on  average)

You leave out the most important reason:
3- Higher TL societies have more to lose! As technology increases, so 
does the destructive power of its weapons.  The Cold War did not become a 
hot war because neither side was pushed by confrontation (indeed, they 
avoided confrontation) into a situation where they felt the only 
alternative was to lash out - since they knew that lashing out would be 
the last thing either side did.

many disagreements among the greater powers in the 20th century would 
have lead to war in the 19th or certainly the 18th century.  As teh Costs 
of war rise, the willingness to engage in a full-scale war decreases.  
WWII taught the nations of earth how destructve war could be - and how 
costly its clean up afterward.  Complete with a hint of how awful the 
next upgrade of weapon technology could be...

As TL rises, abd weapon destructive ness rises, nations risk more by 
going to war against an equal opponent - hence they avoid it where they can.

					Ted7


