Actually, the Imperial Warrant was *real*.  The only thing that Norris
forged was his "appointment" to Archduke Deneb in 1116.  The Warrant
was one of those "here\'s your rope; don\'t go hang yourself" situations. 

In the context of the 5FW board game, the Imperial player doesn\'t get 
all the admirals.  The "real" 5FW was played out with Sector Admiral
Santanocheev as the highest ranking admiral available, as I recall.
So Goolanzoon and Mtume aren\'t available.  Norris is the only other
Imperial admiral that has a zero planning time.  Santanocheev was 
sacked, in game context, because his planning time was too slow, and
this would let the Zhos make it look like they were doing one thing,
