  {
    'id' => '<950630111304.21a16846@centum.utulsa.edu>',
    'ts-index' => '1995-06-30.ab520',
    'date' => 'Fri, 30 Jun 1995 11:13:04  0500 (CDT)',
    'body' => 'I would say that Psionic Invisibility would let the Psi (in this case Droyne)
be completely invisible to affected observers. However, his movement will
be recorded - if he leave the area, you will see his tracks in the dust,
and
if a camera was running, you will see him scurrying across the way.
Furthermore,if the camera was feeding to other observers (in a ship, for
instance) and
the Droyne could not psionically affect them, *they* would see the Droyne,
but the cameraman on the ground would not - though the GM might permit an
additional roll, or a roll with a bonus, to detect the Droyne.

Hmm, that was longer than I thought it would be. :)


J Roberson
