TL-8 Odour Supplant-Janitorial Robot [OS-JR]
 
The Odour Supplant-Janitorial Robot [OS-JR], commonly called 
Hos-Jar, was one of the first models introduced to the vacated 
automated maintenance & upkeep market in the Reformation 
Coalition.  Hos-Jar has been developed and manufactured back in 
mid-1200 by a small and unknown company called Barzel Manufactory 
[BM]. 
 
Barzel Manufactory started out in early 1200 as a family run 
electronics repair facility, which provided its services to the 
expending population of Delios Tradestation, Apollo\'s orbiting 
Class-E Starport. Due to Apollo\'s status as an Administrated 
Territory by the Reformation Coalition, there were barely any 
restrictions in the way of design and implementation of robotics by 
the RCSA.
        
This cemetery world provided Barzel Manufactory with most of the 
components and electronics needed, thus supplying virtually a free 
and a steady replenish of scavenged electronic apparatus.  Many 
market analysers, on Aubaine and elsewhere in the coalition, 
attribute it as the reason for their relatively high pitched 
earnings in sales. 
 
                        ----
 
Barzel Manufactory first released this model in an attempt to 
suppress the growing numbers of vermin in Delios\'s inner hull and 
service conduits.   They produced a small array of Hos-Jars to 
patrol and exterminate the vermin.  The Hos-Jar\'s low and 
semispherical hull, together with it\'s tiny arm enabled it to reach 
into the vermin\'s hideouts easily and brought to a successful & 
triumphant victory.  
 
Thus, the first introduction of Barzel Manufactory\'s robots designs 
became a favourite addition in Delios.   Their celebrated high 
speed chases after vermin in the empty fuel tanks resulted in 
numerous gambling pools in the bars.  Scores were kept for each 
Hos-Jar\'s performance, and later, even a tri-d Hos-Jar simulator 
game was released by Barzel\'s expending venture into the 
electronics commodity market.
 
Hos-Jar successfulness in controlling the vermin situation also 
attracted a number of transient Free Traders and Coalition 
Merchants to acquire the model for treatment on their vessels and 
as merchandise to trade around the coalition.  It is also rumoured 
that some Guild vessels obtained the model, but this information is 
not conformed.
 
Of course, exterminating vermin was only one component of Hos-Jar 
multi-operational capacity.  Barzel Manufactory added many 
diversified optional odour canisters to their Hos-Jar product line 
and transform it to an Air quality enforcement tool.   
 
For example, here\'s Barzel Manufactory\'s ad for the Hos-Jar:
 
"...be it in a marines\' changing room after a raid, aboard a 
scout ship with a shabby lavatory or a Ithklur-infested bar 
with no elbowroom, even in the maintenance bays of Aubaine\'s  
Starport, Odours can make you and your customers feel 
uncomfortable and interfere with their enjoyment of your 
facility and products.   That means loss of revenue and 
produces a bad name for your business.   
 
-So how can I solve the problem?, you ask.  
 
Why, here at Barzel Manufactory, we came up with the 
appropriate tool for the job.  Our Odour Supplant Janitorial 
Robot product will attack at an unwanted odours and restore 
the air quality to your normal standards.  The Hos-Jar, as we 
fondly call it here, uses a low  body configuration and a 
quiet operational mode to keep it out of view. It\'s swift 
movement will reach any area where it\'s services are needed 
quickly and effortlessly.   
 
The Odour Supplant Janitorial Robot model is also easy to 
maintain and inexpensive to own.   Of course, we back all our 
products with Barzel Manufactory\'s standard 20 years warranty 
so you don\'t have to worry about a thing. Our full catalogue 
of various Odours and pesticides add-on canisters is available 
at no charge.   Whichever odour you need, we can supply you 
with it.  
 
Our company offices and product exhibitions are available at 
most major starports (Aubaine, Trybec, Aurora and our new 
offices in the Kruyter system) and of course, you can always 
reach us at Barzel Manufactory\'s main offices:
 
Barzel Manufactory
Airlock 8, Delios Tradestation 
Apollo, Reformation Coalition
[Barzel_Manufactory@lock8.delios.ap.rc]"  
 
           - Extracted from _The Coalition Onward Gazette_, 
             Barzel Manufactory\'s ad, p. 9.
           - Issue XII/1201, Trantown, Aubaine.
 
                        ----
 
Physical & Technical Description:
 
The Odour Supplant-Janitorial Robot model utilise a low, 
semispherical shaped composite laminate hull which provides 
its main structural support.  A short arm is based on the top 
of the hull, housing the odour emitter mechanism and a tube 
which is attached to the externally mounted odour/pesticide 
canister at the rear of the hull.  The arm\'s installation 
resembles a turret, with the ability to turn 360 degrees, thus 
providing an superb coverage of the area around the robot.   
 
A basic visual sensor is installed towards the front of the 
hull, just below the arm\'s installation.   It provides the 
robot with basic pattern recognition;  For example, the 
Hos-Jar will recognise Humans, walls, Hivers and everything 
else in its way as obstacles.  Although, it could also be 
pre-programmed to track a specific configuration, colour or 
smell of an obstacle.  Be it a rat, Ithklur or a foul-smelling 
vac suit, the Hos-Jar will distinguish it and spray it if 
so programmed.
 
The Smoke/Gas Detector sensor is installed alongside the basic 
visual sensor.  As described before, it can be pre-programmed 
to detect a specific odour/smoke/gas, follow the programmed 
instructions and handle it.   Located underneath these two 
sensors is the internal speaker.   This device can be 
pre-programmed with a small number of Anglic words and it comes 
with miscellaneous other options like Male/Female voice, voice 
volume and more. (Note:  Barzel Manufactory recently announced 
the availability of alternative sound cards for the Schalli 
and Ithklur languages).   
 
The Hos-Jar\'s TL-10 storage battery provide for its power 
requirements and is installed internally at the base of the 
hull, just below the CPU brain unit.  The battery is the only 
component used in this model that is manufactured & shipped to 
Apollo from Trybec instead of being scavenged from Apollo 
itself.   This high performance battery provides for 5 hours 
of continuous operation and is easily recharged.
 
And last, The Hos-Jar\'s robot brain unit.   This state of the art, 
TL-8, unit is produced solely from the finest recovered components 
available.  It resides on top of the battery, and is easily 
accessed by lifting the arm\'s installation.   The housing contains 
the CPU unit and the varied sensory pre-programmed cards.   The 
brain is occupied with Barzel Manufactory\'s patented PRAC/1 
[Pattern Recognition Algorithm Card, Class 1] (As discussed above, 
regarding the basic visual sensor).  
 
All of the cards, including the brain, can be easily programmed 
using a TL-8+ hand/standard computer, the owner\'s password and the 
MCE [Module Customising Extension], located on top of the CPU 
unit.   Just plug-in the cord to the computer\'s standard port and 
Hos-Jar\'s brain will display the options that are accessible to you.
 
                        ----
 
Referee\'s Notes & Adventure Hooks:

The Hos-Jar can be added to most Traveller/Megatraveller/Traveller: 
The New Era campaigns readily and can provide for a broad & richer 
atmosphere & background in the adventure.   The Odour Supplant 
Janitorial Robot is designed to be used as an NPC by the referee.   
Be it a minor encounter in the bar, or a mini-adventure on its own, 
here are some tips which can help you run the Odour Supplant 
Janitorial Robot Model by Barzel Manufactory in your Traveller 
adventure.
 
If you look closely at the Design Notes, you might notice that the model 
suffers from a shortage of power. This 0.000008 MW shortage is not 
obvious during normal operations, since not all of the components 
work at the same time.   However, if the power requirement is 
stretched to its limit i.e.: If the Basic Visual Sensor and the 
Odour/Gas Detector, plus the Odour Emitter, arm and the brain start 
to operate simultaneously, unknown effects might occur.    The main 
reason for this is that the brain is the main power hog in the 
model, thus it will be the one developing minor quirks in its 
operation.
 
These quirks can range from simple ones, for example, the brain 
won\'t shut off the gas emitter, thus, flooding the bar with sweet 
aroma which will irritate a group of Vargrs.  This will provoke them to 
pursuit the Hos-Jar down and destroy it, causing a commotion which 
may lead to various adventure hooks.  
 
- The owners wants the Vargrs to pay for his 20,000Cr Hos-Jar which 
  they destroyed and hires the PCs to find them and obtain the money 
  from them.
 
- The PCs help the Vargrs out by shutting off the Hos-Jar (in a 
  friendly way), thus gaining the gratitude of the Vargrs/Bar owner 
  which may lead to miscellaneous rumours/job offers.
 
- [More to come...]
 
Another problem with this model is that the arm can only handle a 
load of 480g while the Gas Emitter installed on it weight 500g.   
This problem plus the poor agility of the arm (AGL 2) can be used 
by the referee to turn them into either witty scenes
or terrifying ones.  For example:
 
- [more to come...]
 
