1. 5FW and Santanocheev

Norris called him "that buffoon" in "Survival Margin", and the SMC book says
that Santanocheev was working off invalid info given to him by the ONI (in
my campaign, my players refer to them as "The Offal of Naval Intestines",
indicating that they are held in high regard (not!). The ONI were apparently
convinced that the Zhos were organising a major push thru Efate, rather than
the Abyss Rift. Consequently, he was in the process of diverting ships away
from Rhylanor - which would have been disastrous.

2. Interdicted Droyne worlds

I think that the xboat316 reply was right - they were interdicted when the
Imperium discovered that they were psionic. Also, the Imperium believed that
one of these worlds was the Droyne homeworld - potential threats from
still-functional Ancient super-weapons would be a walid reason for
interdiction, don\'t you agree?

3. Droyne Invisibility

My bet is for the "Plateau eyes" effect (_A Gift From Earth_, Larry Niven) -
the
victim ignores the Droyne totally. This agrees with Andy Lilly\'s response #3,
Rob Prior and J Roberson.

- Hyphen
