6/7-95 Mark Wilson Barrows wrote:

>What is the functional difference between low berths and
>emergency low berths in MegaTraveller?  The only hard
>info I have found on low berths is on page 82 of the
>Referee\'s Manual, and that only shows the differing
>power requirements, volume, mass and cost.

The ordinary low berths are for travelling just like stated
in the rules. Emergency low berths are for, yes, just that,
emergencies. They differ from ordinary low berths in at
least two ways:

1. I don\'t remember where it says this, although Starship
Operators Manual would be a good guess, but
emergency low berths can hold 4 persons at a time.
Of course they all have to be frozen at the same time.
This is the main reason for the difference in volume, etc.

2. Emergency low berths freeze people very quickly and
thaw them very slowly, where ordinary low berths both
freeze and thaw at a moderate pace. There\'s a trade-off
between time required for freezing and time required for
thawing. This is all detailed in the article about low berths
in TD 21(?).
As far as I remember, every low berth can be set to act
as other types, but they come with a standard setting.
With emergency low berths one would assume that the
highest priority would be to be frozen as fast as possible,
hence the setting with fast freeze time and slow thaw time.
With low berths for a frozen watch, for example, freeze time
is very slow and thaw time very fast, because what matters
is that one can get replacement troops as fast as possible.

Mark Seemann
ms@oem.dk
