    'body' => 'Dear Folks -

OK, here they are: my (almost) complete house rules for missiles (pre-TNE).
It was an attempt to integrate _THE LOT_!! Oh well, here goes:

----
Modified _Missiles_ for _Mayday!_ or _HG_

1. SUMMARY OF COMPONENTS
========================
a. Propulsion System
   Propulsion Assembly = Assembly Casing + Fuel Mass
        - continuous burn
        - limited burn
        - discretionary burn

b. Guidance System
   1. Controller
   2. Sensors - radio receiver/radar sensor
              - IR sensor
              - mass sensor
              - neutrino sensor

c. Detonation System
   Detonator - contact
             - proximity
             - intelligent
             - command

d. Payload
   1. Warheads - conventional HE
               - improved non-conventional shaped explosive
               - TDX
               - blast-producing nuclear warheads
               - enhanced radiation nuclear warheads
   2. Non-weapon payloads - flare
                          - probe
                          - message

e. Internal Power
   Power Source - batteries
                - fuel cell

f. Standard turret missile container

2. DETAILED COMPONENTS
======================
a. Propulsion System
                  Mass (kg)            Price (Cr)
   Continuous     Mc = G               100 x Mc
   Burn           Mf = T x G           50 x Mf

   Limited        Mc = 5 + G           200 x Mc
   Burn           Mf = T x G           100 x Mf

   Discretionary  Mc = 10 + G          50 x G^2
   Burn           Mf = 0.4 x T x G     200 x Mf

   Mc = Mass of casing; Mf = Mass of fuel;
   G = G-rating req\'d; B = Number of turns req\'d

b. Guidance System
   1. Controller
      TL   Mass (kg)  Price (Cr)   Power req\'d (kWh)
       8     3        450             1.5
       9     2        300             1.0
      10+    1        250             0.5
