    'body' => 'Some good sources:

Uller Uprising by H. Beam Piper - the essay at the front contains
biochemistry (or is this a flourine world? can\'t remember)

Analog - several articles by Dr. Stephen Gillett - including one on chlorine
breathers (October 1994, pp 60-70).  Contains details on biochemistry - you
can\'t just replace oxygen with chlorine (the chemical energies are too weak),
but you can have a chloride-oxygen hybrid biochemistry that works well.  This
is a really good article - I strongly suggest you find it (or an equivalent).
 Dozens of story/adventure ideas (including accedental infection of \'normal\'
worlds with chlorine-releasing lifeforms). 

Gillett notes that you can\'t simply pick similar valences without doing
energy calculations.  

"An icy planet, with seas laced with acid for antifreeze, and an atnosphere
containing Cl2, CO2, and perhaps nitrogen - maybe it exists somewhere."
