    'body' => 'Glenn <ggoffin@igc.apc.org> wrote:

> In what other ways have you handled or heard of handling
> deep space rendezvous?  

The Traveller Adventure involves the PCs in a tradewar scenario, wherein 
they are given the coordinates of a Tukera deep-space rendezvous (for 
their jump-1 Hercules transports, etc.). So jumping to a given, 
prearranged point in deep space is canonically possible.

Since mini-jumps are possible, it follows that jump distances can be 
controlled with a bit of finesse. Even without a gravity well to pull one 
out of jump, arranging a rendezvous w.r.t. the centre of mass of each of 
three visible stars ought to work well enough -- as long as you want to 
be found at the rendezvous.

