    'topic' => 'Waterworld (the movie)',
    'body' => 'It seems to me that Waterworld must be rather a stupid 
movie, because I\'ve solved it by watching the preview.  
(Maybe it\'s no more stupid than other Hollywood 
blockbusters, but I just missed those previews.)

Anyway, the preview indicates the following:  In the
future the earth has become covered by water.  The movie
concerns the search for the last spot of dry land.

Now if the level of water has risen enough to cover the
earth, it will do so evenly, and the places with the
greatest elevation will be the last covered -- so Mt.
Everest should be the last spot above water.  The latitude
of Mt. Everest is known, and latitude can be determined
with simple navigational instruments (I think just a
sextant).  So Mt. Everest will have the highest population
density and tightest security of any spot on the planet.

Now I suppose from the preview that the water level 
increased because the ice caps melted, but I leave for 
others to figure out whether there is actually enough water 
there to raise the water level nearly six miles.

The only other scenario that I can imagine for increasing
the water levels is that a meteorite with sufficient
displacement falls into the ocean.  Then maybe part of the
meteorite would be sticking above the water.  In that
scenario, all human life (and most other life above insect
level of complexity) would surely be destroyed by the
earthquakes and nearly instantaneous flooding.  In
addition, the planet would probably be knocked out of its
orbit, with dire effects on the climate (for colder or
warmer).  (Of course, any survivors would have kept track
of where the meteorite hit, and would find it with simple
navigation once it cooled.) 

Am I missing something here?  Should I see this one on the 
off-chance that I\'ll get a good idea for a Traveller 
campaign (I\'ve just run an episode on a waterworld, but it 
wasn\'t a post-holocaust type of thing).

Albert and John:  If you reply, please don\'t reply to the 
cc:, which is a mailing list related to a role playing 
game called Traveller.

--Glenn
