    'date' => 'Sat, 5 Aug 1995 10:46:04  0700 (PDT)',
    'body' => 'The following is a list of either novels and/or anthologies that were 
written by George R.R. Martin and are set within his Traveller-like universe.

"Tuf Voyaging" - An anthology of seven short stories all dealing with the 
                 adventures of Haviland Tuf aboard his starship "Ark".
                 [In the hardcover edition a sequel is mentioned as being 
                 in the works, but has still not appeared after several 
                 years.]


"Dying of the Light" - Novel set upon a rogue planet (Worlorn) and deals 
                       with the interactions of members of several alien 
                       human cultures. This book gives an indepth view of 
                       the  culture and customs that evolved on 
                       High Kavalaan during its era as a lost colony.
 
"Nightflyers" - An anthology with the primary story set aboard a cybernetic 
                starship of the same name. This particular story was made 
                into a movie. Another Traveller like story in this 
                anthology is "And Seven Times Never Kill Man" - Great 
                short story that deals with a small colony of 
                Steel Angels ( a quasi-religious movement advocating 
                Human Supremacy over all other life-forms...sound 
                familiar???). 

"Portraits of His Children" - Anthology with the following Traveller stories:
                              "With Morning Comes Mistfall" - One of the 
                              best, mainly because I am in this story.  =)
                              This particular short story strongly 
                              reminded me of the Keith brothers 
                              adventure, "Ascent to Anekthor". "The Glass 
                              Flower" - This story deals with a legendary 
                              figure within Martins universe, a cyborg named 
                              Kleronomas, who was instrumental in ending 
                              the Interregnum that followed the Collapse.

"A Song for Lya" - Another anthology. "Override" is set on the planet 
                   Grotto, and involves the happenings of a small swirlstone 
                   prosprctor. "The Hero" - This story is takes place 
                   during the Federal Empire, just prior to the Collapse.
                   It involves the "early retirement" of a soldier from the 
                   war-world Wellington. "A Song for Lya" - Post 
                   Collapse, set on the world Shkeen. Deals with a pair of 
                   psionic "Talents" (trouble-shooters) and their encounter 
                   with an alien "god".

"Windhaven" -  A novel, coauthored with Lisa Tuttle and my personal favorite 
               after "Tuf Voyaging". The setting for this novel is on  
               Windhaven, a low gravity, dense atmosphere waterworld that is
               home to a lost colony of humans who survived the crash 
               landing of their \'generation\' starship. The story revolves 
               around the Flyers Guild, a caste that binds the scattered 
               island outposts of Windhaven together.
               


Placing Martin\'s Universe within Traveller.

A careful reading of Martins work shows that the planets in his 
universe lay rimward of Terra, in an area that he calls the "Fringe". In 
Martins own words, "...the starchats of the Fringe, that scattering of 
thinly settled worlds between the smoke-dark gasses of the Tempter\'s Veil 
and the Great Black Sea itself."  Some of his worlds are set on the 
coreward edge of the Tempter\'s Veil (which is a dark nebula/rift). One 
world, Tober-in-the-Veil, lies within the nebula/rift itself. Most however, 
are located in the Fringe proper. The extreme rimward edge of the Fringe 
is also known as the Last Stars, and these worlds stand sentinel over the 
intergalatic void, the Great Black Sea.

Somewhere, I have compiled "Library Data" for all of Matrin\'s Universe. 
If anyone is interested in obtaining a copy, let me know. I hope some 
have found this post interesting =)

Will scrape hulls for Low Passage,
Paul Sanders

P.S.  TNE = Traveller? Not Even!
