    'topic' => 'taxation, cont\'d',
    'body' => 'Further to my posting on taxation and citizenship:

Territories directly controlled by nobles, including both the 
barony/marquisate/county/duchy and the fief, are taxed in accordance with 
the patents of nobility and enfoeffment.  These patents are not subject 
to much negotiation, and can be truly ruinous to the noble.  This is one 
way of neutralizing enemies of the Emperor.  Normally, however, getting a 
barony/etc. and a fief means a life of extreme material comfort (not a 
life of no work, mind you, but the best working and living conditions, at 
least at the physical level).

--Glenn Goffin

