    'body' => 'Dear Folks -

Paranoia Press were a UK company who wrote some Traveller books, under
licence
from GDW. This gear dates from the (very) early 80\'s. Donald Rapp ran the
company; Chuck Kallenbach (sp?) wrote Vanguard Reaches.

These included:
        The Beyond       } sector background ala Supplement 3: Spinward
Marches
        Vanguard Reaches }   "       "        "      "      "     "        "
        SORAG            } details on a Zho covert body (equiv CIA, MI5, KGB)
        Scouts and Assassins } PC expansions, prior to Book 6: Scouts
        Merchants and Merchandise } Pc Expansons, prior to Book 7: Merchants

In Scouts and Assassins, they detailed the aircraft-shaped Type S Scout, as
built by "Delta Research" of the Beyond. The Beyond showed where they were
located. Merchants and Merchandise came up with some nifty equipment as well
as the PC expansion, including a low-tech grav bike, a tranq gun (this was
prior
to Book 4\'s snub pistol), a taser, intelligent (AI) computers partially built
with organic components (experimental TL 16), medical low berths, and even
transporter booths (!! experimental TL 16, 17!!).

The subsector maps, I believe, are no longer seen as "canon". I believe that
they were viewed as "excessive" in nature, perhaps not fitting in with
"normal"
Traveller (eg. one or two TL\'s in the Beyond!). I know that Chuck re-wrote
the
Vanguard Reaches a few years ago, saying that "wild rumours" about
ringworlds,
etc (there was one in the Beyond) were just that - wild rumours.

I admit, I liked the Reaches better than the Beyond. A nice touch was a
nebula in subsector M, being studied by a research station.

(I also found some WEIRD coincidences, BTW: In my version of Far Frontiers,
I placed Thieves World about 4 hexes from where Chuck had placed it in the
Reaches; plus, I made the nation spanning Foreven and Beyond (SEE the
standard
black "overall" map) a Germanic one - and this was before I knew it had
been named "Die Weltbund" in the Beyond! Dah duh dah duh dah duh dah duh...)

- Hyphen
  (David Jaques-Watson)

