Revolver (good quality): $300-500

"Automatic" (self-loader): $450-600  (a typical Glock \'ll run you $575
here in Albuquerque, for example).  East european autos can be had in
the $150 (Makarov) and up range (9mm P9R, $250).

Shotgun: $250 (pump)

SMG:  $1000 (I\'m not so sure, I don\'t shop for these since I don\'t have
a Class III Federal Firearms Licence)

All of the above are new prices.  Used will be, um, 50% off for good
ones (assuming they aren\'t rare, or otherwise "extra" valuable).

Various semi-auto military styled rifles run from cheap chinese SKSs at
$150 to nice AR-15s at $1000-1500 (a buddy of mine has an HBar----nice
gun to shoot).

A WW2 vintage bolt action can be had for $100 (a British SMLE, or No.1
Mk4), my \'44 Mauser 98kar was $250.

Pistol ammo runs $10 for 50 rounds, rifle ammo is more like $10 for 20
rounds.  Modern rifle ammo is pistol priced (5.56mm for the M-16 is
pistol priced, and AK-74 ammo would be as well).

-Merrick
