ratio of support systems to actual ships is of the order of 5:1 or worse.

That is, the naval budget includes starports, depots, shipyards, support
staff (civilians), salaries, ship maintenance, software purchase and
development, R&D, fuel refineries and storage, etc etc. You\'ll find that
in any navy, the amount spent to buy the actual vessels is quite small
in comparison to the overall budget.

