    'ts-index' => '1995-09-20.ab781',
    'body' => '>A quadrillion is 1,000,000 trillions, right? How many people would that
>support assuming that it was all spent on imperial salaries? Assuming an
>average salary GNPof 25.000 Crimp it comes to 40 trillion people, or close
>to 3 times the entire populantion of the imperium!

..that\'s why I should write out numbers around here. :)  I use the
American number terminology, so a quadrillion is a thousand trillions 
and a quintillion is a million trillions (10^15 and 10^18 respectively).
I know that a fair number of XTML readers do use different conventions
for Really Big numbers, but maybe I was feeling reckless. :) 

I\'ll divide the figures for Imperial GNP by the figures for population to 
get an estimate of Imperial GNP per capita:

(CT/Striker)  According to the old TML article, Derek got a population of
16.73 trillion; he got a GNP of TCr 219500.  That\'s Cr 13100 per person
at 16.73 trillion, or if we assume a population of only 15.73 trillion,
Cr 14000 per person.  

(TNE/WTH)  I estimated population at 15.77 trillion.  Again, assume that
the figures that I came up with earlier are in tech-12 credits.  I got a 
GNP of TCr 538000 in tech-12 starport-B credits, or TCr 430000 in 
Imperial (tech-15 starport-A) credits.  That\'s Cr 27300 per person in 
Imperial credits.

In MegaTraveller, there\'re rules for upkeep costs in the Player\'s Manual.  
Annual upkeep for an "average" person of SocSt 7 is Cr 21000.  This does 
not cover equipment like a new ground car or hand computer; it only 
includes food, lodging, clothes, and incidentals.

A quick look over the WWW found that the USA has a GDP per capita of
US$ 24700, one of the highest of the industrial nations.  The lists
of equipment prices in MegaTraveller suggest that the figures I am
getting above are reasonable. 

(Note:  I think a real economist would use "GDP" to refer to what I am
calling GNP, but they\'re for our purposes virtually identical.)

  Steve Bonneville
