    'from' => 'Alun Moon A.J.Moon@newcastle.ac.uk',
    'body' => 'As a few people have asked to look at the fuel tables I have constructed 
for book 2 drives.  The consumption details still need a little work, 
they are based on the "Beltstrike" module GDW produced.



The fuel use table below gives the fuel tankage required for each type of
drive.  In some cases this is more efficient than High Guard, in others
less so.  I will confess to a little bias, I like small ships so the jump
fuel table is very efficient at the lower end for the first few drives.

This changes the basic starship designs;

The Type-S Scout has the following changes...

    1.  Fuel capacity is now 33 tons (two jumps plus 4 weeks) 
    2.  Cargo capacity is now 6 tons

  The effect of the changes means that the Scout has a little more cargo
capacity, but the main change is the range.  The Scout can now perform two
jumps at maximun range, this has two advantages

    1.  The Scout can now traverse the X-Boat route, albeit at half the
       speed of an X-Boat 
    2.  The Scout can make a return trip of jump-2 in range without
       refueling.

  These two effects are compatable with the Scouts role as part of the
X-Boat service and as an exploration craft.  In fact they make the
Scout more viable in these roles.

The Type-A Free Traider changes as follows...

    1.  Fuel capacity is now 18 tons
    2.  It now carries an Air-Raft
    3.  It now has a cargo capacity of 90 tons.
       The original 82 tons hold, and a`Special Cargo Area\' of 8 tons
       attached to the main hold.

  These changes make the Type-A compatable with that portrayed in the
`Starship Operators Manual\'.  The increse in cargo capacity (8 tons) is the
size of the "Special Cargo Area" on the upper cargo deck.  See the plans in
the `Starship Operators Manual\'.


Fuel for Book 2 drives
  Power plant fuel (4 week supply)
  ----
  Type |  A |  B |  C |  D |  E |  F |  G |  H |  J |  K |  L |  M |
  Tons |  3 |  6 |  9 | 12 | 15 | 18 | 21 | 24 | 27 | 30 | 33 | 36 |
  ----
  Type |  N |  P |  Q |  R |  S |  T |  U |  V |  W |  X |  Y |  Z |
  Tons | 39 | 42 | 45 | 48 | 51 | 54 | 57 | 60 | 63 | 66 | 69 | 72 |
  ----

  Jump fuel (One jump at maximum rating)
----
Type |  A  |  B  |  C  |  D  |  E  |  F  |  G  |  H  |  J  |  K  |  L  |  M
Tons |  15 |  30 |  45 |  80 | 100 | 120 | 160 | 200 | 225 | 250 | 275 | 300
----
Type |  N  |  P  |  Q  |  R  |  S  |  T  |  U  |  V  |  W  |  X  |  Y  |  Z
Tons | 325 | 420 | 450 | 480 | 510 | 540 | 570 | 600 | 630 | 660 | 690 | 720
----


The actual consumption is as follows...
  Jumps use the fraction of the fuel as the fraction of the jump to
        the jump rating of the starship.

  Power Plants use fuel as follows, 0.007 tons per day,  
        (0.05 tons per week) for each drive letter.

        Book 2 power plants produce an actual output of 1ep per ton of
        fuel tankage required.
        (The power plant rating number reprisents the power density of
        the starship,  ep\'s per 100 tons) 
        (see High Guard for the ep-fuel conversion (1ep=250MW))

  Manoeuver fuel used in manoeuvering is used at the rate of 
        0.002tons/hour per G per 100tons.
        (0.05tons/day or 0.35tons/week)


