    'from' => 'Erich Schneider',
    'body' => '
I was wondering if any of you who have more Latin than I (my high
school Latin teachers are undoubtedly tsk-ing right now) might
translate the motto on the 2610 Rule of Man quarter-credit coin in the
Solomani Alien Module. It appears to be:

DOMINATUS HOMINIS SPLENDET SPLENDIDE AMPLIUS QUAM GLORIAM ASTRIBUS

I have always found the picture of this coin to be one of the more
compelling illustrations in all Traveller works; a relic of a
long-lost optimistic age when the uppity Terrans thought they could
bend anything to their will, but learned the hard way that the Vilani
ran their empire the way they did for good reasons.

-- 
Erich Schneider  erich@bush.cs.tamu.edu  http://bush.cs.tamu.edu/~erich
