    'date' => 'Mon, 02 Oct 95 12:48:00 PDT',
    'body' => 'Re:  Droyne, I would guess that Droyne would only obey Leader caste 
individuals from their own oyntrip.  Oyntrips can and are often at odds with 
one another at a number of levels, ranging from friendly mercantile 
competition to all-out war.  A Worker or a Warrior would not be trusted (or 
even trust himself) to judge whether or not a given order might work against 
the interests of his own oyntrip.

Now, if one oyntrip conquored another, the conquoring leaders would probably 
be obeyed without question once they were established.  This would be similar

to the situation in RANGER: 2300, where conquored Ebers actually need the 
direction of their conquorers in order to survive.

----Gar Francis
     UCLA, Islamic Studies and Sophontology.

