  Based on other canonical sources, the impact is illness rather than 
insanity - jumpsickness is almost always fatal.  Note that uptures in the 
jump grid can allow jumpspace to intrude into the ship, sucking folks out 
into the void.  Not a nice way to go.

  I don\'t have access to my back issues of Challenge, but there is a 
Traveller News Service report that referes to the first person to survive 
jump outside a ship (in a vac suit).  Perhaps someone with this info can 
look this up.
 
