> transitions: Where you are going and when you\'ll arrive; and also if you\'ll
> experience different time than the universe as a whole. And it only lasts a
> minute or two!
> 
> Damaging the hull grid is a great way of eliminating a ship\'s crew and
> passengers, though. They\'ll be insane before they drop out if you can
> damage the grid enough. Just make certain you\'re not aboard...

  It is possible to repair the breeches in the grid during flight, though 
it is tough.  The starship operators manual talks about this, I think.

