> I\'m looking for an official or semiofficial answer to the following...
> You are in jump space and your jump drive shuts down cold (suppose
> someone just disconnects the power supply).  What happens?  Do
> you immediate emerge from jump space (now that you are being "held"
> in it) at some random location?  Or do you not get out until the
> drive is fixed (since you can\'t "push" you way out.)  Or do
> you just come out some random time later in some random
> location.  (Or do you just all die? :-)

Here\'s some thoughts on this one.

Briefly, the failure of the Jump-Drive mid jump should result in the ship 
misjumping. (roll 1D, roll that number of D parsecs, in a random 
direction 1D on the sector maps).  To be fair to my players, I drop the 
ship into the nearest system, if the above process lands them in an empty 
spot on the map.  The misjump rules though do occasionally destroy a 
ship, on a roll of 18+ (from 2D with modifiers).

I\'ll wrap this up in some "science" and post that a little later.

