Anything as sophisticated as a field generator that alters the dimensions of
space-time can fail, especially if it is not maintained correctly or
frequently.

The thing that disappoints me about the description of hyperspace and
j-space in FF&S is the absence of reference to time as a dimension of space.
Denial of relativity is not necessary for the playability of the game if one
allows for the ability to alter space-time or make reference to a time
dimension. 
I don\'t like the descriptions of hyperspace and j-space that sound as if the
game is Spelljammer of AD&D and j-space is some kind of magical poisonous
ether. 
Adding a 3D aspect to the game doesn\'t make it less attractive of less
playable and nor should making reference to relativity if one builds in
systems that compensate for its affects. 

