    'body' => 'Dear Folks -

In Xboat 408, David J. Golden replied to my Droyne missive:

>        Sounds a lot like the Moties from "The Mote In God\'s Eye," by Niven
>and Pournelle. The Moties developed a Mediator sub-species to negotiate
>between Masters.

Let\'s face it, the Droyne _are_ the Moties. Both have a rigid caste system
and different "sub-species" (Worker, Warrior, Technician, whatever). Many
things in Traveller can be traced almost directly to s-f novels, for
example much of H. Beam Piper\'s work (the Sword Worlds, the "Space Vikings"),
Niven, Pournelle, Heinlein (eg "Starship Trooper"). Some s-f novels can be
traced to Traveller (for example, in my opinion, David Drake\'s "Hammer\'s
Slammers", "The Forlorn Hope", etc).

My point about the motivation of Droyne leaders was just that it is
similar in many ways to the motivation of Protectors. The actual conduct
of two alien races has been portrayed quite differently. For example,
the Droyne do not seem to be the type to want to wholeheartedly
slaughter mankind - but the Protectors who are not human probably would.

- Hyphen
(David Jaques-Watson)

