    'index' => 'ab839',
    'month' => '10',
    'body' => 'This subject may already have been discussed, so just a 
pointer to the archives may be all I need.

What "prefixes" do ships use in the CT/MT universe?  For
example, United States Navy and merchant ships are called
"U.S.S. Ship Name"; British navy ships are "H.M.S. Ship
Name"; some countries use "M/V Ship Name", and other
variations exist.  Is there any more or less canonical set
of prefixes (aside from the unwieldy five-letter prefixes
used by FASA:  I.S.P.M.V. Tethys, etc.)?

A question precedent, I suppose, is where or with whom are
the ships registered? in the Imperium, with the Imperium
itself (probably) or with individual worlds? how do other 
entities handle ship registration?

Obviously, a great many abbreviations could be generated
(Imperial Navy, Scouts, civilian; Zhodani Navy and
civilian; Aslan families; zillions of Vargr states;
Solomani Navy and civilian; Vegans; Hivers; Kkree; Ardenian 
Defense Force; etc.).  Has anyone tried to set a standard?
'
