    'month' => '10',
    'index' => 'ab851',
    'body' => '
What are the ranges of starship weapons?

What kind of defense is there against ships jumping in to a system
and firing immediately?

Since light travels relatively slow, planet-bound targets won\'t 
detect the enemy until enemy fire has already reached them (since
energy blasts also travel at the speed of light).  

What\'s to prevent a battleship from jumping-in to a system and
immediately firing its weapons at premapped planetary targets?


If they fire from far away, it could conceivably take 10 or more 
minutes for the blasts to reach the planet.  By the time the planet
fires back, the attacking ships could easily jump back out of system,
or change vectors.

These questions came to me in the midst of designing a new space combat
system.  Your thoughts would be most appreciated.

Food for thought,
Hyperodge
