    'topic' => 'Space combat in _Invasion: Earth_',
    'body' => 'I\'m looking for some "war stories" from players of _Invasion: Earth_
about the space battle.

By a simple count it appears the Imperium outnumbers and outguns the
Solomani in terms of fleet strength initially. It would them seem that
if the S. tried a strategy of stacking the whole fleet in the close
orbit box and telling the I. "come and get it", the I. could attrit
away the entire defense force and still have enough transport capacity
to transport the entire ground force to Terra in two waves (this
requires four transports and 6 BatRons, since there are 5040 I. troop
points including the 10 bases). Moreover, they can then do planetary
landings and bombardment without harassment (except for PD units).

It then seems to me that the space battle would go like this:

1) S. divide their forces into an attrition group, a group to hide in
the deep space box, and a group to hide in the oceans.
2) I. attrits away the attrition group.
3) S. harasses the I. player with the "deep space" group and uses the
ocean group to help the PD units.

Is this more or less what happens? I\'ve never played the game; I
bought it used some months ago, and have been looking at it recently.
(Actually, I\'ve never played Traveller in any form except for one game
of _Imperium_, but I have a large collection...)

-- 
Erich Schneider  erich@bush.cs.tamu.edu  http://bush.cs.tamu.edu/~erich
