Unstreamlined vessels can\'t survive a landing... they won\'t be spaceworthy
after such a landing... but if their thrust is good enough and the pilot is
hot enough, alerted crew and passengers should be able to survive the
landing. Remember that a 2G thrust rating indicates the ability to take up
to 2 G\'s of force along the primary thrust axis.

On an USL (unstreamlined) hull, the problem is that the hull is stressed
for RCS thrusters and the primary thrust axis ONLY. So if you carefully
burn down (like the apollo and viking landers), you could probably even
save the atmospheric integrity! For CT ppurposes, this probably requires an
11+ on 2d6, DM+ pilot skill, DM+1 for dex 8+.

