support it\'s own weight.  I figure if a ship can survive hits from 
missiles which will knock it around at over 10 Gs, it can survive 
planetary gravity.  Maybe a dispersed structure would have some trouble, 
but I think just about anything else would be fine.  The only advantage 
of streamlining is the ability to fight in atmosphere and move about 
quickly in it.  Unstreamlined ships do not routinely land because it 
would take on the order of 5 to 10 hourse to do so.

