    'from' => 'Andrew Madden amadden@pcug.org.au',
    'body' => 'I believe what is meant by Von Neumann machines is \'self-programming\' not 
necessarily self-replicating. This is a technology which is a form of AI, 
and according to canon should be listed at TL17+. Basic forms *might* be 
available earlier.

Regarding Nanites, I would guess that they would appear at roughly TL9. 
These would be basic robotic non-sentient machines which would require 
programming and control from a proximate computer via radio waves, or 
perhaps HF low amperage electrical stimulus. Or perhaps chemical triggers 
to set off certain pre-programmed functions. At TL9 this would be 
experimental and extremely expensive. It would probably be TL10 or 11 
before they become more widespread (perhaps to leading edge health care 
facilities). They would still be prohibitively expensive. I think it 
would be a few tech levels later for broader production. Perhaps TL16/17 
for mass production?

I would say it would be TL20 -25 before you saw a Von-Neumann Nanite.

All views expressed about nanites are of course arbitrary decisions made 
with respect to game balance from my perception. Any other views would be 
