    'body' => 'Hi there! (This is Eddie you shipboard computer)

I have another question that I would like to hear some discussion on
(or a reference it there are already rules on this sort of thing)

Would it be possible to have a jump missle?  Imagine the following 
situation.  A border patrol ship is on a patrol (or is inside the
oppositions border) when it is attacked.  The ship is alone and is losing 
the battle (several of the enemy ships appeared and want to use the 
system as a staging area).  The captain of the doomed ship wants to let
his goverenment know that its border is no longer secure and so...
HAZZAH... uses a jump missle.  The jump missle is dropped (or launched--
possible pneumaticly) by the ship (from a suitable bay to house such a 
device) at which time it enters jump (having been preprogramed by the
ships computer and in radio link with it until jump is entered).  Once
the missle reached its destination, it would emerge and begin transmitting
whatever message it had been programmed with.  (Assuming it would be sent
to a friendly system) the knowledge that borders had been breached would
be known much earlier than would be otherwise.  (Basically, it would act 
like an xboat with no pilot, life support, passageways, etc...   Could
such a device be made small enough to be placed in a small enough bay to
make it worthwhile)

Comments and criticisms welcome

Thanks

Tom Trelenberg
