    'body' => 'Hi there

Although a Jump missile is not allowed under CT/MT rules, such a thing was
included in a CT adventure (Adv 4:Leviathan), where a one-shot
jump-capable message torpedo was provided.  I tried to fit this in with
the canonical rules, eg. saying that actually the 100+ displacement rule
wasn\'t completely correct; there was a sort of "bubble" of usuable volumes
at the very small scales, where you could fit a jump drive and send the
resulting device through jump. Unfortunately (so my rationalisation went),
the result was that the torpedo barely survived the travel through jump,
and was only able to transmit a burst of information before going
completely to pieces once it emerged from jump.  Couple this to a
posulated high expense, and obvious low security, and possibly low
reliability (high propability of never leaving jump space in one piece,
etc.) , explains why the Imperium uses the expensive Xboat/Scout/Courier
network (not very satisfactorily, though).  I really would have liked to
keep jump torpedoes in CT, but I think it really plays havoc with some of
the basic assumptions.  I think I decided to leave out this idea in 
Leviathan, which is a pity, because it is a nice idea.

