    'body' => '
I hate to contribute to this thread again, but....

STARSHIPS AS "JUMP MISSILES"
----

Roger Sanger commented:

>Even though a "jump missile" might be impossible, surely
>a starship could be converted into an unmanned kamakazi
>device -- in practical terms, a jump missile.

Amber Zone: "A Dagger At Efate", BJTAS #2 (selected from JTAS #5-8).
The mercenary cruiser _Dagger_ returned to the Efate system on course
for the mainworld, but isn\'t acknowleging hails from control.  The
players\' ship is ordered to investigate.  The ship is deserted, but
Auto/Evade is active in the computer, and it is locked on a course
that will cause it to crash into the largest concentration of Imperial
troops and supplies on Efate.  Internal evidence in the adventure
suggests that the ship has about a 2 G-turn vector as it approaches
the planet, as I recall.


OFFICIAL ROCK-THROWING
----

It turns out that there are official references to rock-throwing in
classic Traveller, as planetary bombardment.  High Guard mentions 
that empty bays can carry "deadfall ordnance", useless in space combat
but used in planetary bombardment.  The "Battle Fleets of the Marches"
article by Marc Miller mentioned that most CruRons have an auxiliary
"bulk ordnance carrier" attached to them to carry missile reloads for
the CruRon -- but in some cases, a *second* bulk ordnance carrier is
attached to mine small moons and planetoid belts for large rocks and
asteroids that will be used in the planetary bombardment phase of
an assault. 

A ship dropping deadfall ordnance could go onto an impact vector with
the target, shove the rock(s) gently out of the empty bay(s), and fly 
away, leaving the rock in the merciless hands of physics.  They might  
not be as effective as missiles, but they\'re a lot cheaper and readily
available on site in quantity.  You don\'t even need a mass-driver,
since the whole ship can be used as a big mass-driver.  This only
works if your target can\'t get out of the way, of course. 

  Steve Bonneville
  <bonn0015@tc.umn.edu>

