9/11-95 Rob Flammang wrote:

>        But Jump Torpedoes ARE cannon. They can be
>found in the CT adventure "Leviathan" published by
>GDW. They do not damage the background of Classic
>Traveller; they are an indispensible part of it. The
>challenge is to come up with an explanation consistent
>with canon why jump torpedoes are POSSIBLE. There are
>no design rules for them as far as I know. Rules need to
>be made that mesh well with existing starship design rules
>so that players can fully explore the potential of these
>devices. The problem is that design rules from Book 2,
>Book 5, Striker and MT are not consistent with one
>another.

Yes, I _know_ that "Leviathan" contains jump torpedoes.
What I was trying to say in my last message is that
canonical sources are not mutually consistent (now where
have I seen that before :-)). The MT rules explicitly states
that a vessel, in order to be a starship, _must_ be larger than or equal to
100
 displacement tons.

All I\'m trying to say here is that we can discuss this issue
from now till hell freezes over, and keep hitting each other
in the head with quotes from different canonical sources.
But we are playing to have fun, and each referee can run
his or her campaign excactly as he/she likes it. _I_ don\'t
view "Leviathan" as a source that I can use (canonical or
not), because it conflicts with the way _I_ read other
canonical sources. Other people may view this entirely
differently, and that\'s okay with me. Let\'s not make a
religous war out of this.

I\'m just saying that the way _I_ read the MT canon, jump
missiles doesn\'t make much sense to _me_.

Mark Seemann
ms@oem.dk
