    'index' => 'ac030',
    'month' => '11',
    'body' => 'Hi.  One problem with jump torps is they have serious effects on the game 
universe.  While one can play around with the canonical sources a bit and 
make them fit on the "fictional physics" level, this does not address 
certain important questions.  For instance:

1) Why have an X-boat network for delivering mail?  Why not just have a 
bunch of mass-produced little jump-6 torpedoes speeding all over the 
universe?  They could even carry some types of very small cargoes.  And 
they would be much cheaper.

2) Why not put some payloads on these jump torps and just send buckets of 
them into enemy systems as a cheap attack strategy (though it provide 
little more than harrassment, I don\'t know)?

This is not to shoot down jump torps, I just feel one has to deal with
such issues if one wants to include them in the Traveller universe.  An
interesting possibility someone brought up recently is that jump torps
have low survival rates (e.g., half of them don\'t make it through jump
space).  This might make them impractical for an empire\'s regular
communications network, but handy for emergency situations. 

Charles.

