probably leading to a new war.

The Vegans were well on there way to being conquered by the late 1120\'s.  
However, it may have regained it\'s freedom if the Solomani fractured as 
badly as people on TML/XTML seem to feel.  I persponally suspect that the 
Solomani would have simply reconquered it\'s Sphere, and then focused it\'s 
expansion efforts rimwards.

The Domain of Deneb would have been somewhat deal smaller than the Regency 
at 1200.  By the time the fighting there stopped, all Imperial holdings 
in Trojan Reach and Reft Sector would have been lost, although more of 
Deneb would have been recovered, at least to Segan. 

(sorry, but I\'m  following offical GDW history regarding the Aslan/Vargr 
ivasions, rather than admitting that - given our knowledge of their 
demographics and technology - any such invasion is impossible)

Very few pocket empires (The Covenant of Sufren, maybe?) would have 
