the ___&____ series consists of two books that I am certain were released:
_Vilani & Vargr_ and _Solomani & Aslan_. The third was to be _Zhodani &
Droyne_.
These were done by Digest Group Productions, under liscence from GDW, and
supplanted the individual race modules of the classic set. They are
specific to MT, but as with all things MT, conversion to CT is minimal.

Note that some future confusion may arise out of GDW\'s current release,
_Hiver and Ithklur_, which is nothing more than the old hiver book, with
New era conversions for CGen, and the Ithklur, who seem to have been added
purely for comic relief.

The DGP materials were the best alien modules I have worked with for any
gaming system, ever. They are complete, and give a wide range of detail
(they\'re almost 3/8" thick), and well laid out.

By comparison, the CT modules are good, but too short. The TNE aliens so
far are not taken seriously enough to allow PC\'s.

-Wil

