    'date' => 'Tue, 05 Dec 95 13:03:00 PST',
    'index' => 'ac150',
    'month' => '12',
    'topic' => 'paired alien modules',
    'body' => '_Vilani & Vargr_ and _Solomani & Aslan_ were part of a series of alien 
modules which DGP planned to put out, but they got out of TRAVELLER stuff 
before they could finish the series.  The series tried to pair a human race 
with an alien race (the ones which were never published were _Zhodani & 
Droyne_, _Hivers & K\'Kree_, and _Minor Races_).

V&V and S&A brought things up to date for MEGATRAVELLER added material that 
wasn\'t in the original alien modules.  Some of this new information was 
useful (details on homeworlds, history from the race\'s point of view), but a 
lot of it was bullshit new rules just designed to add more bells and whistles

that really weren\'t needed (giving Vilani REALLY long lifespans, inventing 
variant Vargr races, giving Aslan pseudo-psionic powers).  For my money, the 
original alien modules are best, and it\'s easy enough to come up with your 
own conversions.  Of course, that\'s if you can find and afford them.  I saw a

copy of _Droyne_ going for $22 at a con last year!  (Does anybody know what 
copyright laws are for materials that are out of print?)

GDW has started coming out with alien modules for New Era, but like 
everything else, it\'s going v...e....r...y  s...l...o....w...l...y.  I saw 
_Hivers & Ithklur_, and it\'s interesting, but there\'s also a lot of stuff 
that contradicts CT/MT cannon and I don\'t like NE anyway.  Does anybody know 
if the _Regency Sourcebook_ gives us much of an update on the races in the 
Spinward Marches (Vargr, Zhodani, Droyne, LOTS o\'minor races)?

'
