    'body' => '<Michael.Barry@FINANCE.ausgovfinance.telememo.au> wrote:

> 5.  What happened to the Imperium\'s borders while the fleet admirals were
> off eating each others\' tails around Capital? During the civil wars of the
[...]
> contributed nicely to further instability. SOMEBODY had to be maintaining
> the borders against the Vargr, Solomani, Aslan, etc other than Arbellatra. I
> can\'t imagine the nasties being particularly impressed by the news that
> Arbellatra\'s navy away off in the Spinward Marches would come along and
> spank their botties if they invaded...

The Aslan would be constrained by the Peace of Ftahalr, which predates the
First Civil War, if by nothing else.

The Solomani Sphere, at least as far out as the Near Bootes Cluster, was
fully integrated into the Imperium by this period.  We know for certain
that Terra, and probably the rest of the Old Earth Union, was admitted in
588.  Beyond the Imperial border would have been a collection of fairly
advanced but small states of Solomani origin, similar to the OEU and the
Easter Concord, a number of individual worlds, and an open frontier.  The
Solomani Confederation doesn\'t exist until 871.

The Vargr.  Hm.  Well, the Vargr in Gvurrdon moved with the Zhodani based
Outworld Coalition in the 2FW, but we don\'t know if anything happened in
other places along the border.  Since all the barracks emperors were "pure
Solomani", and the region along the border is very Vilani in nature except
for the Marches, parts of Deneb, and maybe parts of Antares, maybe most
of those fleets stayed put.  Generalized unrest along the border, caused
by Vargr corsairs, wouldn\'t be surprising though.

The K\'kree are too far away -- their jump drive technology probably lagged
the Imperium even worse in the 600s than it does in the 1100s.  The Hive
Federation would rather trade with the Imperium and the non-aligned states
than invade anyone.

  Steve Bonneville
  <bonnevil@itlabs.umn.edu>

