     <Do you have a list of  known ancient sites, especially in the Domain of
Deneb?>   The following is part 2 of a file by Clay Bush on the ancients:

                             Regina Subsector

Yori
(University of Regina)

   This small site is characterized by iridescent white building
blocks and occasional deep rubble-filled wells.  It was found
buried in a vast desert, surrounded by signs of destruction from
the Final War.

Beck\'s World
(University of Regina)

   Somewhat larger than the Yori site, it is a collapsed warren of
interlocking caverns.  It is only partially excavated.

Efate
       (IISS)

   Operated as a historic site.  Restorations show a gridwork of
thousands of walls spaced about two meters apart, and punctuated by
extremely massive bulwarks at random intervals.
   Discovered in 354, it has long since been stripped of any useful
items.

Pixie (Secret)
       (IISS)

   A flat irregular area meticulously inlaid with a mosaic of
multi-colored anodized aluminum bars.  There is no sign of the
purpose of this site.
   Located on the edge of a vacuum plain under the shadow of a
range of mountains, the site is protected by numerous security
devices.

Inthe (Secret)
       (IISS)

   Large artificial mounds of earth, tens of kilometers long, are
scattered over a thousand square kilometer, but analysis and
excavaton has given no indication of their purpose.  A large
volcanic crater (now water-filled) lies on the plain in the center
of the mounds, and may have been the site of the Ancient base.

Knorbes (Secret)
(Imperial navy)

   Ruined brick and mortar buildings here held a large cache of
2,000 black globe generators.  The Ancient base was originally
destroyed when a massive attack cratered the area, and then toppled
mountains into the craters.  In the thousands of years since,
erosion has uncovered the site.
   The navy has taken elaborate precautions to conceal the fact
that a site even exists here.  Similarly elaborate measures trap
and detain intruders.

                              Lanth subsector

Boughene (Destroyed)

  The ship destroyed itself after the adventure, Secret of the
Ancients.  The village and navigation beacon were reported to the
authorities.

Victoria (Lanth 0207)

   In 1077, Vlen Backett found an Ancient site in a clearing,
apparently a residence.  "Later, Backett loved to tell about the
wonders and magics he had found in that little warren of rooms and
closets.  His descriptions of the shimmering walls, The doors of
cloud-mist, the floors of focussed gravity, the paper-thin but
steel strong partitions, the many fantastic sights and sounds were
he himself admitted, inadequate."
   The site on the moon had been looted long before 1077.


                            The sites at Zhdant

   In -302,000 a fleet of droynestarships arrived in the Zhdant
system and within the space of a year or two established two
settlements or bases.  Once the bases were established, the fleet
of ships left.  Their further adventures are unknown.
   Over the next century, the two bases grew into cities.  Each
city created a thriving economy, and they traded goods between
them.  Orbital stations were established on asteroids moved into
place for the purpose.

   Zhdant City sprawled along the western coast of Qiknavra,
creating large networks of rail-guided grav transports, skyscrapers
in the western mountain ranges, and undersea dome cities off-shore.
The ancients dug gently curving trenches miles into the floor of
the ocean, and then gently filled them in.  They sliced off the
tops of mountains, lifted them twenty meters into the air, and
filled the gaps with artificial stone.  They built large reinforced
steel buldings totally empty and totally sealed against entry.
   The inhabitants also bred humans until the local human
population approached 500,000.  Evidence indicates they were a sort
of trained servant/pet.

   The other settlement occupied a wind-swept desert plain on the
eastern limb of Zhdant\'s tidally locked moon - Viepchakl.  The
foundations of Viepchakl city burrowed kilometers into the the
crust of the moon; its towers reached heights of ten kilometers.
Familiar activities include many identical buildings and a tunnel
network carrying utility servicing.
   Arrow straight roads tunnelled through intervening rock faces
without flinching, but stopped or were abandoned when confronted
with crevasses or chasms more than a few meters deep.  Desert sands
were sorted into stockpiles based on color or granular shape.
Viepchakl city shows no evidence of ever having kept or bred
humans.

   The two cities did have one common feature: in both cities, road
intersections were marked with a stone stanchion topped with a
polished crystal octahedron.

   Zhdant in the Final War.  The war was late in touching Zhdant.
Radioactive dating methods place the first nuclear explosion at -
299,700.  Nearly 500 megatons rained down on Zhdant City in a few
days.  The orbiting asteroid station was knocked from orbit,
crashing into the ocean and burying itself in the sea floor.
  Viepchakl City\'s buldings were cut off even with the ground, and
allowed to shatter when they fell.The city center become one big
crater kilometers across - although the weapons used left no
measureable radiation contamination.
   The attacking fleets left within a few weeks.  There is no
evidence of further attacks in the system.  Bacteriological agents
specific to each city\'s inhabitants were drop-launched, but were
each went to the other world.  This was discovered only when
Zhodani astronauts brought the two into contact in -7,950.

   Dust thrown into the Zhdant\'s air caused a nuclear winter, which
triggered an ice age.  In a short 20,000 years the glaciers began
to retreat.  The descendants of human survivors began the long
climb to civilization.


